{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2819"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of other general-purpose machinery"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2819"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :general-purpose-machinery/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :equipment-safety :weighing-accuracy-integrity :quality-defect-transparency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :general-purpose-machinery-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :eda :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies []
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "WeighPkgAdvisor ⊣ General-Purpose Machinery Plant Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for ISIC 2819 (Manufacture of other general-purpose
 machinery), the RESIDUAL general-machinery class (weighing/packaging
 machinery, gas generators, fire-extinguisher equipment, and other
 general-purpose machinery not elsewhere classified) -- this build
 picks ONE concrete illustrative product line, documented plainly in
 the README: industrial weighing/packaging-machinery manufacturing
 (platform scales, checkweighers, batching scales, filling machines,
 wrapping machines, labeling machines) -- assembly and calibration-
 test-bench lines producing finished weighing/packaging machinery --
 not direct assembly/calibration-line-equipment control authority and
 not legal-metrology or machinery-safety certification authority (e.g.
 OIML R76 / NIST Handbook 44 legal-for-trade weighing-accuracy
 certification, or EU Machinery Directive 2006/42/EC CE conformity /
 ANSI PMMI B155.1 packaging-machinery safety marking). Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD
 invariants: propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed
 proposal-effect allowlist (no direct assembly/calibration-line-
 equipment control), permanent equipment-actuate block, permanent
 legal-metrology/machinery-safety-certification-authority block (this
 actor never self-issues an OIML R76/NIST Handbook 44 legal-for-trade
 weighing-accuracy certification or a CE/ANSI-PMMI machinery-safety
 conformity mark), independent equipment verification/registration
 before maintenance scheduling, independent batch verification/
 registration before shipment coordination, independent shipment-
 quantity recompute against the batch's own logged production
 quantity, double-schedule guard, product-type validation, calibration-
 accuracy plausibility validation, and defect-rate plausibility
 validation. Safety-concern flagging (equipment-safety/quality-defect
 concern) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant supervisor;
 `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and
 only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
